    • Method Detail

      • run

        void run​(String taskName,
         ParallelExecution.ThrowingRunnable... runnables)
  throws Exception
        Runs the given tasks with a thread pool with a fixed number of threads, which is the number of threads given to this ParallelExecution instance at construction time. The number of jobs may exceed this number.
        Parameters:
        taskName - name that the spawned threads will get.
        runnables - jobs to run.
        Throws:
        Exception - on any job exception.

      • runAll

        void runAll​(String taskName,
            ParallelExecution.ThrowingRunnable... runnables)
     throws Exception
        Runs the given tasks with a thread pool with number of threads set to the number of tasks. I.e. all the given jobs will be run concurrently.
        Parameters:
        taskName - name that the spawned threads will get.
        runnables - jobs to run.
        Throws:
        Exception - on any job exception.
